  -One folder for all documentation, one file for each week of documentation.
  -If person can't make it to a meeting, send message in Teams chat, and write in their own progress in documentations

Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates):
  [if you adopt such a policy during the initial meeting, put it here]
  -All changes should be made in your own branch
  -Whenever you want to commit to main branch, send message asking people to check in teams chat, people check code before scrum meeting, then talk about whether to 
    commit to main branch during scrum meeting
  
Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations:
  must include at least 3 actions before involving the instructor:
    -Person who is not making an effort to meet expectations - Consistently skipping meetings:
      1.] Talk to them about it
      2.] Enforce certain amount of 3 commits per week
      3.] Pair Programming
      
    -Person making an effort to meet expectations:
      1.] Talk to them about it 
      2.] Offer resources 
      3.] Pair programming - two or more can program together
      
      
